Manufacturing Flow:
1. Token composition sub-flows
2. Manufacturer by component to widget ratio is assigned
2. legalOwnerShipToken (EIPxxx?) is minted
3. Ownership terms signoff by composition & order size. This can be a systemic trigger to indicate the confirmation of production of the goods

Rights Token Flow:
1. Token (de)composition sub-flows for associating rights token ownership
2. rightsOwnershipToken (EIPxxx?) is minted and transferred to Carrier
3. Ownership terms signoff by composition & order size

Shipping Token Flow:
1. Token (de)composition sub-flows for associating rights token ownership, and shipping costs
2. shippingOwnershipToken (EIPxxx?) is minted with bill of lading info and transferred to buyer
3. Ownership terms signoff by composition & order size

Delivery Confirmation Flow:
1. Token (de)composition sub-flows for associating rights token ownership
2. rightsOwnershipToken (EIPxxx?) is transferred to buyer
3. Ownership terms signoff by composition & order size

Payment Token Flow:
1. net30ReceivableToken is a part of the payment terms in the PO sent in Step 8a
2. paymentToken (EIPxxx?) is minted and transferred to supplier, which also contains the payment terms
3. Ownership terms signoff by composition & order size

Dispute Management Flow:
1. net30ReceivableToken is minted and transferred to supplier(?)
2. paymentToken (EIPxxx?) is transferred to buyer, based on oil price of the date of delivery
3. Ownership terms signoff by composition & order size (after re-association)

Calculation Flow:
1. Interface with Oracle contract to get the current oil price, based on currency
2. Update quote based on place of manufacturing, baseline price per supplier, and assumed limits for per widget price decline and oil prices
3. Assumption of committed minimums

Winning Supplier Flow:
1. Choice based on committed minimums
2. Lowest priced supplier is to be given the higher volume order

Note: Onboarding/set up flow is a separate timing digram, and will be interfaced at the beginning and over the duration of the procurement life cycle. This includes any authentication of identities both for public as well as private attributes/functionalities
